<br>
Believe me if I could change things I dont think I would be a guild leader again.<br>
<br>
Our guild is young and small compared to the others on our server. We were even voted the #8 guild to &quot;F off cause we where noobs&quot; on our servers rants board. which I thought was funny as hell.<br>
<br>
I recently have had many people leave at once due to they wanted a guild with &quot;more&quot;. Which I thought I was giving them. I tryed so hard to make everyone happy in our guild and inturn made my game a nightmare. To the point I didnt even want to play anymore.<br>
<br>
I sat down and talk to 2 other guild leaders kinda like ours.<br>
<br>
They told me dont try and make everyone happy ... Try and give your members what the marjority wants. Talk to them see what they want and ask them what makes them happy.<br>
<br>
What it came down to was not everyone wants the same out of the game.. You just have to find members who share your mission statement whatever that may be.<br>
<br>
<br>
We are now in the process of doing it. I am once again a happy GL and wouldnt give up my Knights for anything in the world.<br>
<br>
Just remember you cant make everyone happy. Just give them a good stable sense of direction and it should fall in place.<br>
<br>
I'm not the best GL but Our guild is growing and we have a good ole time when we are all on and about! For us its all about fun!<br>
<br>
